{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":880,"text":"Today, I want to tell you\nabout a pressing social issue."},{"time":4720,"text":"Now, it's not nuclear arms,"},{"time":7080,"text":"it's not immigration,"},{"time":8680,"text":"and it's not malaria."},{"time":10640,"text":"I'm here to talk about movies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14120,"text":"Now, in all seriousness,\nmovies are actually really important."},{"time":18480,"text":"In film, we can be wildly entertained,"},{"time":22680,"text":"and we can also be transported\nthrough storytelling."},{"time":27480,"text":"Storytelling is so important."},{"time":29320,"text":"Stories tell us what societies value,"},{"time":32880,"text":"they offer us lessons,"},{"time":34880,"text":"and they share and preserve our history."},{"time":38080,"text":"Stories are amazing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40440,"text":"But stories don't give everyone"},{"time":43400,"text":"the same opportunity\nto appear within them,"},{"time":47880,"text":"particularly not stories"},{"time":50360,"text":"compartmentalized\nin the form of American movies."},{"time":54520,"text":"In film, interestingly enough,"},{"time":56840,"text":"females are still erased and marginalized"},{"time":60440,"text":"in a lot of our stories."},{"time":62520,"text":"And I learned this for the first time\nabout 10 years ago"},{"time":65400,"text":"when I did my first study\non gender role in G-rated films."},{"time":69200,"text":"Since then, we've conducted\nmore than 30 investigations."},{"time":72800,"text":"My team is tired."},{"time":74680,"text":"And I've committed my life"},{"time":78080,"text":"as researcher and activist"},{"time":80600,"text":"to fighting the inclusion crisis"},{"time":83320,"text":"in Hollywood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85200,"text":"So today, what I'd like to do\nis tell you about that crisis."},{"time":88720,"text":"I want to talk about\ngender inequality in film."},{"time":91320,"text":"I want to tell you how it is perpetuated,"},{"time":93720,"text":"and then I'm going to tell you\nhow we're going to fix it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97760,"text":"However, one caveat before I begin:"},{"time":101600,"text":"my data are really depressing."},{"time":104960,"text":"So I want to apologize in advance,"},{"time":107040,"text":"because I'm going to put you all\nin a really bad mood."},{"time":110200,"text":"But I'm going to bring it up at the end,"},{"time":113600,"text":"and I'm going to present a silver lining"},{"time":116480,"text":"to fix this mess that we've been in"},{"time":118880,"text":"for a very, very long time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":121480,"text":"So, let's start with the gravity\nof the situation."},{"time":125440,"text":"Each year, my research team\nexamines the top 100 grossing films"},{"time":129080,"text":"in the United States."},{"time":130720,"text":"What we do is we look at every speaking\nor named character on-screen."},{"time":134960,"text":"Now, to count in one of my investigations,"},{"time":137920,"text":"all a character has to do is say one word."},{"time":142120,"text":"This is a very low bar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":146200,"text":"Thus far, we've looked at 800 movies,"},{"time":148640,"text":"from 2007 to 2015,"},{"time":150680,"text":"cataloguing every speaking character\non-screen for gender, race, ethnicity,"},{"time":155560,"text":"LGBT and characters with a disability."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159920,"text":"Let's take a look\nat really some problematic trends."},{"time":163800,"text":"First, females are still\nnoticeably absent on-screen in film."},{"time":168400,"text":"Across 800 movies\nand 35,205 speaking characters,"},{"time":172760,"text":"less than a third of all roles\ngo to girls and women."},{"time":176480,"text":"Less than a third!"},{"time":177800,"text":"There's been no change from 2007 to 2015,"},{"time":181280,"text":"and if you compare our results"},{"time":182733,"text":"to a small sample of films\nfrom 1946 to 1955,"},{"time":187400,"text":"there's been no change\nin over a half of a century."},{"time":191720,"text":"Over half of a century!"},{"time":193120,"text":"But we're half of the population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195760,"text":"Now, if we look at this data\nintersectionally,"},{"time":198600,"text":"which has been a focus of today,"},{"time":200760,"text":"the picture becomes even more problematic."},{"time":203880,"text":"Across the top 100 films\nof just last year,"},{"time":206920,"text":"48 films didn't feature one black\nor African-American speaking character,"},{"time":211240,"text":"not one."},{"time":212520,"text":"70 films were devoid of Asian\nor Asian-American speaking characters"},{"time":216760,"text":"that were girls or women."},{"time":218200,"text":"None."},{"time":219840,"text":"Eighty-four films didn't feature one\nfemale character that had a disability."},{"time":224240,"text":"And 93 were devoid of lesbian, bisexual\nor transgender female speaking characters."},{"time":230840,"text":"This is not underrepresentation."},{"time":234040,"text":"This is erasure,"},{"time":235960,"text":"and I call this\nthe epidemic of invisibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240800,"text":"Now, when we move\nfrom prevalence to protagonist,"},{"time":244520,"text":"the story is still problematic."},{"time":247000,"text":"Out of a hundred films last year,"},{"time":248640,"text":"only 32 featured a female lead\nor colead driving the action."},{"time":253280,"text":"Only three out of a hundred films"},{"time":255440,"text":"featured an underrepresented\nfemale driving the story,"},{"time":259240,"text":"and only one diverse woman"},{"time":261560,"text":"that was 45 years of age or older\nat the time of theatrical release."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266320,"text":"Now let's look at portrayal."},{"time":268920,"text":"In addition to the numbers you just saw,"},{"time":270880,"text":"females are far more likely\nto be sexualized in film"},{"time":274520,"text":"than their male counterparts."},{"time":276280,"text":"Matter of fact, they're about\nthree times as likely"},{"time":278720,"text":"to be shown in sexually\nrevealing clothing,"},{"time":280760,"text":"partially naked,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and they're far more likely to be thin."},{"time":284600,"text":"Now, sometimes, in animation,\nfemales are so thin"},{"time":288360,"text":"that their waist size approximates\nthe circumference of their upper arm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293040,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294720,"text":"We like to say that these gals\nhave no room for a womb"},{"time":298160,"text":"or any other internal organ."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300760,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302800,"text":"Now, all joking aside,"},{"time":304400,"text":"theories suggest, research confirms,"},{"time":306360,"text":"exposure to thin ideals\nand objectifying content"},{"time":308760,"text":"can lead to body dissatisfaction,\ninternalization of the thin ideal"},{"time":312600,"text":"and self-objectification\namong some female viewers."},{"time":317040,"text":"Obviously, what we see on-screen"},{"time":319040,"text":"and what we see in the world,"},{"time":321040,"text":"they do not match."},{"time":322800,"text":"They do not match!"},{"time":324080,"text":"Matter of fact,\nif we lived in the screen world,"},{"time":326360,"text":"we would have a population\ncrisis on our hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330800,"text":"So, as soon as I recognized\nthese patterns,"},{"time":332880,"text":"I wanted to find out why,"},{"time":334160,"text":"and it turns out that there are\ntwo drivers to inequality on-screen:"},{"time":338080,"text":"content creator gender\nand misperceptions of the audience."},{"time":341200,"text":"Let's unpack them really quick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":342960,"text":"If you want to change\nany of the patterns I just talked about,"},{"time":345920,"text":"all you have to do\nis hire female directors."},{"time":348400,"text":"Turns out, the female directors"},{"time":350440,"text":"are associated with,\nin terms of short films and indie films,"},{"time":354960,"text":"more girls and women on-screen,"},{"time":356800,"text":"more stories with women in the center,"},{"time":359440,"text":"more stories with women\n40 years of age or older on-screen,"},{"time":364000,"text":"which I think is good news for this crowd."},{"time":366920,"text":"More underrepresented --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368880,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370240,"text":"Sorry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":371480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":373280,"text":"Sorry but not sorry."},{"time":374560,"text":"More underrepresented characters\nin terms of race and ethnicity,"},{"time":378240,"text":"and most importantly,"},{"time":379560,"text":"more women working behind the camera"},{"time":381960,"text":"in key production roles."},{"time":384080,"text":"Easy answer to the problems\nthat we just talked about."},{"time":387840,"text":"Or is it?"},{"time":389080,"text":"It's actually not."},{"time":390880,"text":"800 films, 2007-2015,"},{"time":394160,"text":"886 directors."},{"time":395760,"text":"Only 4.1 percent are women."},{"time":399400,"text":"Only three are African-American or black,"},{"time":402320,"text":"and only one woman was Asian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405520,"text":"So why is it so difficult"},{"time":409040,"text":"to have female directors"},{"time":410840,"text":"if they're part of the solution?"},{"time":413520,"text":"Well, to answer this question,"},{"time":415320,"text":"we conducted a study."},{"time":417120,"text":"We interviewed dozens of industry insiders"},{"time":419440,"text":"and asked them about directors."},{"time":421880,"text":"Turns out, both male\nand female executives,"},{"time":425720,"text":"when they think director,"},{"time":427400,"text":"they think male."},{"time":429000,"text":"They perceive the traits of leadership"},{"time":431880,"text":"to be masculine in nature."},{"time":434160,"text":"So when they're going to hire a director"},{"time":437360,"text":"to command a crew, lead a ship,"},{"time":439680,"text":"be a visionary or be General Patton,"},{"time":442080,"text":"all the things that we've heard --"},{"time":444360,"text":"their thoughts and ideations pull male."},{"time":447840,"text":"The perception of director or a leader"},{"time":450320,"text":"is inconsistent\nwith the perception of a woman."},{"time":454000,"text":"The roles are incongruous,"},{"time":456040,"text":"which is consistent with a lot of research\nin the psychological arena."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460200,"text":"Second factor contributing\nto inequality on-screen"},{"time":463360,"text":"is misperceptions of the audience."},{"time":465960,"text":"I don't need to tell this crowd:"},{"time":467640,"text":"50 percent of the people\nthat go to the box office and buy tickets"},{"time":470920,"text":"are girls and women in this country."},{"time":472920,"text":"Right?"},{"time":474160,"text":"But we're not perceived to be a viable\nor financially lucrative target audience."},{"time":479520,"text":"Further, there's some misperceptions"},{"time":481760,"text":"about whether females can open a film."},{"time":484880,"text":"Open a film means that if you\nplace a female at the center,"},{"time":487760,"text":"it doesn't have the return on investment"},{"time":489720,"text":"that if you place a male\nat the center of a story does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493440,"text":"This misperception is actually costly."},{"time":497120,"text":"Right?"},{"time":498360,"text":"Especially in the wake\nof franchise successes"},{"time":500680,"text":"like \"The Hunger Games,\""},{"time":502800,"text":"\"Pitch Perfect\""},{"time":504040,"text":"or that small little indie film,\n\"Star Wars: The Force Awakens.\""},{"time":509840,"text":"Our own economic analyses show\nthat gender of the lead character"},{"time":513240,"text":"doesn't play a role in economic success\nin the United States."},{"time":516760,"text":"But what does?"},{"time":518080,"text":"Production costs alone"},{"time":519960,"text":"or in conjunction with how widely\na film is distributed in this country."},{"time":526400,"text":"It's not the gender of the lead character."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528960,"text":"So at this point, we should\nall be sufficiently depressed."},{"time":533360,"text":"No change in 50 years,"},{"time":534920,"text":"few female directors\nworking behind the camera"},{"time":537320,"text":"and the entertainment industry\ndoes not trust us as an audience."},{"time":542240,"text":"Well, I told you\nthere would be a silver lining,"},{"time":544640,"text":"and there is."},{"time":546680,"text":"There are actually\nsimple and tangible solutions"},{"time":550000,"text":"to fixing this problem"},{"time":551560,"text":"that involve content creators,"},{"time":553200,"text":"executives and consumers"},{"time":555440,"text":"like the individuals in this room."},{"time":557800,"text":"Let's talk about a few of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559720,"text":"The first is what I call \"just add five.\""},{"time":562200,"text":"Did you know if we looked\nat the top 100 films next year"},{"time":565280,"text":"and simply added five female\nspeaking characters on-screen"},{"time":568520,"text":"to each of those films,"},{"time":569960,"text":"it would create a new norm."},{"time":571600,"text":"If we were to do this\nfor three contiguous years,"},{"time":574400,"text":"we would be at gender parity"},{"time":576440,"text":"for the first time\nin over a half of a century."},{"time":581640,"text":"Now, this approach is advantageous\nfor a variety of reasons."},{"time":584920,"text":"One? It doesn't take away jobs\nfor male actors."},{"time":588880,"text":"Heaven forbid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590240,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":592680,"text":"Two, it's actually cost-effective.\nIt doesn't cost that much."},{"time":596640,"text":"Three, it builds a pipeline for talent."},{"time":598560,"text":"And four, it humanizes\nthe production process."},{"time":601200,"text":"Why? Because it makes sure\nthat there's women on set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605360,"text":"Second solution is for A-list talent."},{"time":608800,"text":"A-listers, as we all know,\ncan make demands in their contracts,"},{"time":612400,"text":"particularly the ones that work\non the biggest Hollywood films."},{"time":616120,"text":"What if those A-listers"},{"time":617880,"text":"simply added an equity clause\nor an inclusion rider"},{"time":622000,"text":"into their contract?"},{"time":624080,"text":"Now, what does that mean?"},{"time":626040,"text":"Well, you probably don't know"},{"time":627760,"text":"but the typical feature film"},{"time":629120,"text":"has about 40 to 45\nspeaking characters in it."},{"time":632520,"text":"I would argue that only 8 to 10\nof those characters"},{"time":635960,"text":"are actually relevant to the story."},{"time":639000,"text":"Except maybe \"Avengers.\" Right?"},{"time":641040,"text":"A few more in \"Avengers.\""},{"time":643680,"text":"The remaining 30 or so roles,"},{"time":646080,"text":"there's no reason why those minor roles"},{"time":648520,"text":"can't match or reflect the demography"},{"time":651440,"text":"of where the story is taking place."},{"time":655120,"text":"An equity rider by an A-lister\nin their contract"},{"time":658720,"text":"can stipulate that those roles"},{"time":661160,"text":"reflect the world\nin which we actually live."},{"time":664480,"text":"Now, there's no reason why a network,"},{"time":667040,"text":"a studio or a production company"},{"time":669240,"text":"cannot adopt the same contractual language"},{"time":672880,"text":"in their negotiation processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675720,"text":"Third solution:"},{"time":677400,"text":"this would be for\nthe entertainment industry,"},{"time":679760,"text":"Hollywood in particular,"},{"time":681000,"text":"to adopt the Rooney Rule"},{"time":683960,"text":"when it comes to hiring practices\naround directors."},{"time":687640,"text":"Now, in the NFL,\nthe Rooney Rule stipulates"},{"time":690280,"text":"that if a team wants to hire a coach\nfrom outside the organization,"},{"time":694160,"text":"what they have to do is interview\nan underrepresented candidate."},{"time":698120,"text":"The exact same principle\ncan apply to Hollywood films."},{"time":702240,"text":"How?"},{"time":703480,"text":"Well, on these top films,"},{"time":704960,"text":"executives and agents can make sure"},{"time":708440,"text":"that women and people of color\nare not only on the consideration list,"},{"time":713680,"text":"but they're actually\ninterviewed for the job."},{"time":717080,"text":"Now, one might say,"},{"time":718600,"text":"why is this important?"},{"time":720040,"text":"Because it exposes or introduces\nexecutives to female directors"},{"time":725280,"text":"who otherwise fall prey\nto exclusionary hiring practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730440,"text":"The fourth solution"},{"time":731920,"text":"is for consumers like me and you."},{"time":735280,"text":"If we want to see more films\nby, for and about women,"},{"time":738280,"text":"we have to support them."},{"time":740480,"text":"It may mean going\nto the independent theater chain"},{"time":743000,"text":"instead of the multiplex."},{"time":744960,"text":"Or it might mean scrolling down\na little further online"},{"time":748480,"text":"to find a film by a female director."},{"time":751080,"text":"Or it may be writing a check\nand funding a film,"},{"time":753960,"text":"particularly by a female director\nfrom an underrepresented background."},{"time":758480,"text":"Right?"},{"time":759720,"text":"We need to write, call and email companies"},{"time":762400,"text":"that are making and distributing films,"},{"time":764282,"text":"and we need to post\non our social media accounts"},{"time":767200,"text":"when we want to see\ninclusive representation,"},{"time":770320,"text":"women on-screen,"},{"time":771600,"text":"and most importantly,\nwomen behind the camera."},{"time":775520,"text":"We need to make our voices heard\nand our dollars count."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781400,"text":"Now, we actually have the ability\nto change the world on this one."},{"time":787640,"text":"The US and its content,"},{"time":790120,"text":"films in particular,"},{"time":791640,"text":"have captured the imaginations\nof audiences worldwide."},{"time":796680,"text":"Worldwide."},{"time":798840,"text":"So that means that the film industry\nhas unprecedented access"},{"time":803240,"text":"to be able to distribute\nstories about equality"},{"time":808280,"text":"all around the world."},{"time":810520,"text":"Imagine what would happen"},{"time":812440,"text":"if the film industry aligned its values"},{"time":816000,"text":"with what it shows on-screen."},{"time":818280,"text":"It could foster inclusion"},{"time":820400,"text":"and acceptance for girls and women,"},{"time":823680,"text":"people of color,"},{"time":825200,"text":"the LGBT community,"},{"time":827080,"text":"individuals with disabilities,"},{"time":828880,"text":"and so many more around the world."},{"time":833520,"text":"The only thing that the film industry\nhas to do is unleash its secret weapon,"},{"time":840080,"text":"and that's storytelling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":843320,"text":"Now, at the beginning of this talk,"},{"time":845720,"text":"I said that films --"},{"time":848160,"text":"that they can actually transport us,"},{"time":850720,"text":"but I would like to argue\nthat films, they can transform us."},{"time":856760,"text":"None of us in this room"},{"time":858680,"text":"have grown up or experienced\na storytelling landscape"},{"time":862960,"text":"with fully realized female characters,"},{"time":866480,"text":"none of us,"},{"time":868000,"text":"because the numbers haven't changed."},{"time":870760,"text":"What would happen\nif the next generation of audiences"},{"time":874880,"text":"grew up with a whole\ndifferent screen reality?"},{"time":879280,"text":"What would happen?"},{"time":880560,"text":"Well I'm here to tell you today"},{"time":882560,"text":"that it's not only possible\nto change what we see on-screen"},{"time":886640,"text":"but I am impatient for it to get here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891400,"text":"So let's agree to take action today"},{"time":895720,"text":"to eradicate the epidemic of invisibility."},{"time":899960,"text":"And let's agree to take action today"},{"time":902280,"text":"to agree that US audiences\nand global viewers"},{"time":906720,"text":"demand and deserve more."},{"time":909880,"text":"And let's agree today"},{"time":912480,"text":"that the next generation\nof viewers and audiences,"},{"time":917680,"text":"that they deserve to see the stories"},{"time":920880,"text":"we were never able to see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924040,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925280,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}